# Character pipeline (in-world)

## Active: one skinned glTF for all NPCs and remote players

- **Asset:** `client/characters/yakuza_shooter.glb` (Mixamo-rigged, embedded clips). Loaded in `create_oyabaun_app` / `Gpu::new`; **no separate rival GLB** in the default path (`character_rival_level` is `None` — boss and rival share the same `CharacterDraw`).
- **Parsing & animation:** `client/src/gltf_level.rs` (skin weights, joints, clip sampling). **Rendering:** `client/src/render.rs` skinned pipeline + per-instance bone upload.
- **Gameplay wiring:** `client/src/lib.rs` maps NPC state → clip indices (idle / walk / run / fire / die) and hit flash via `char_params.w` (`100+h` in `fs_char`).
- **After changing the GLB:** `wasm-pack build --target web` from `client/`.

See **`.cursor/rules/3d-character-integration.mdc`** for clip names, gotchas (mesh_node_world, axis), and Blender source paths.

## Billboards (not for NPCs)

The **billboard pass** in `render.rs` is for **murals / reference backdrop** (`upload_reference_sprite`) and **blood splats** — not for characters.

## PixelLab / sprite atlases (optional, non-NPC)

Legacy `*_atlas.rgba` boss/rival NPC atlases are **removed** from the render path. PixelLab or hand-drawn atlases may still be useful for **HUD weapons**, **muzzle/blood VFX**, or **prop** billboards (separate from NPC mesh). Export: `tools/export_character_atlas_to_rgba.py` if you add new sprite assets.

## Do not (for in-world humanoids)

- Do not reintroduce **NPC sprite billboards** tied to `char_sprite_bg` / atlas rows — use glTF + clips instead.
- Do not add **client-side procedural** character meshes; author in Blender and ship `.glb`.
